I added a `markerClusterer` option in the GMaps constructor, so you can use this way:

``` javascript
  map = new GMaps({
    div: '#map',
    lat: -12.043333,
    lng: -77.028333,
    markerClusterer: function(map) {
      return new MarkerClusterer(map);
    }
  });
```

When you add a marker, the marker clusterer will update automatically the map's viewport.

NOTE: You need to import the marker clusterer library.

