Hi, I found two bugs in your code:

You are using `#map` selector:

``` js
$(document).ready(function(){
  map = new GMaps({
    div: '#map',
    lat: -12.043333,
    lng: -77.028333
  });
});
```

When you have a `#map_canvas` element:

``` html
<div id="map_canvas"></div>
```

Also, you need to set a height for `#map_canvas` (that's mandatory for GMaps and Google Maps too). Check the jQuery UI documentation to see how to set a height in that element.

It depends what kind of geofence do you have. It works when `fence` is an instance of `google.maps.Polygon` or `google.maps.Circle`. It doesn't work with `google.maps.Rectangle` but you can use this polyfill:

``` javascript
google.maps.Rectangle.prototype.containsLatLng = function(latLng) {
  return this.getBounds().contains(latLng);
};
```

